00:33:05.577 --> 00:33:06.578
Who's to say they wouldn't?

498
00:33:06.644 --> 00:33:09.279
That was wrong.
It's not what the cards said.


499
00:33:09.848 --> 00:33:11.716
We were fine in third class.

500
00:33:12.416 --> 00:33:15.285
We don't belong there
and neither does she.


501
00:33:22.359 --> 00:33:23.628
Hmm-mm.

502
00:33:23.661 --> 00:33:26.263
Now then, put that in your pipe.

503
00:33:55.459 --> 00:33:57.595
Have you seen George's new film?

504
00:33:57.795 --> 00:33:59.497
Oh, it's simply divine.

505
00:33:59.731 --> 00:34:01.733
Hepburn lights up every room.

506
00:34:02.332 --> 00:34:03.801
Including the box office.

507
00:34:03.902 --> 00:34:06.504
I don't know how to compare it
to some of his earlier pictures,


508
00:34:06.704 --> 00:34:10.207
probably not as entertaining as
Two Dinosaurs Meet
While Ice Skating.


509
00:34:10.675 --> 00:34:12.042
But it is just magical,
wouldn't you agree?


510
00:34:12.075 --> 00:34:13.511
Excuse me, Sir.

511
00:34:13.545 --> 00:34:14.979
Now, you may ask,
what is the distinction between


512
00:34:15.013 --> 00:34:16.346
subject matter and style.

513
00:34:16.446 --> 00:34:17.949
-But this is a cinematic...
-I'm a dancer.


514
00:34:17.982 --> 00:34:20.450
-...experiment in style.
-I'd to audition for
your next movie.


515
00:34:21.619 --> 00:34:22.620
What now, my dear?

516
00:34:22.654 --> 00:34:23.555
I'm a dancer.

517
00:34:23.588 --> 00:34:25.823
I'd like to audition for
your next movie.


518
00:34:25.957 --> 00:34:28.091
I'm the star
you've been looking for.


519
00:34:32.229 --> 00:34:35.332
Did your parents not teach you
that it is very rude


520
00:34:35.365 --> 00:34:39.537
to come to a table uninvited?
-Oh, Viktor. Come now.


521
00:34:48.312 --> 00:34:50.147
Good evening, your name please.

522
00:34:50.180 --> 00:34:51.783
Mr and Mrs Howe.

523
00:34:52.149 --> 00:34:54.318
Frightfully sorry I had
to cancel earlier.


524
00:34:54.519 --> 00:34:57.120
My wife is feeling
much better now.


525
00:34:57.689 --> 00:34:59.423
Is there a table still free?

526
00:35:08.833 --> 00:35:10.100
What happened?

527
00:35:12.870 --> 00:35:13.871
Oh.

528
00:35:20.778 --> 00:35:23.146
David.

529
00:35:23.180 --> 00:35:25.049
He once asked,
can I give him a scoop?


530
00:35:25.248 --> 00:35:27.819
A scoop, I said, of what
ice cream?!


531
00:35:27.952 --> 00:35:29.053
Well, I'm a sherbet...

532
00:35:29.087 --> 00:35:30.287
Excuse me.

533
00:35:30.955 --> 00:35:32.456
Sir, that's my girl
you just spoke to.


534
00:35:32.489 --> 00:35:35.292
She's, er, just a little upset.

535
00:35:42.533 --> 00:35:43.534
Now...

536
00:35:44.902 --> 00:35:46.638
I apologise that she
interrupted you,


537
00:35:46.671 --> 00:35:50.140
but she wants to be in movies
more than anything and, er...


538
00:35:50.307 --> 00:35:52.010
and now she's just
a little upset.


539
00:35:52.043 --> 00:35:53.978
She's talking about
abandoning her dream,


540
00:35:54.012 --> 00:35:55.680
which upset my wife.

541
00:35:55.713 --> 00:35:57.447
Oh, we're also performers.

542
00:35:59.249 --> 00:36:01.184
Now, she's a dancer.
A very good one.


543
00:36:01.385 --> 00:36:02.620
Better than that Ginger Rogers.

544
00:36:02.654 --> 00:36:04.388
-Oh, she is?
-Oh!


545
00:36:04.421 --> 00:36:07.457
You'll be doing
me a big favour
if you just reconsider.


546
00:36:07.491 --> 00:36:10.061
You, you see what see can do,
you won't be sorry.


547
00:36:22.607 --> 00:36:25.810
Please.

548
00:36:40.457 --> 00:36:41.592
Please.

549
00:36:42.894 --> 00:36:44.829
And who are you?

550
00:36:45.395 --> 00:36:47.330
My thought exactly.

551
00:36:52.436 --> 00:36:54.471
Go home.
We'll reschedule.


552
00:36:54.505 --> 00:36:56.373
Why would you
invite us here
and then tell us to go home?


553
00:36:56.406 --> 00:36:58.042
Isn't the book from
your son's perspective?


554
00:36:58.076 --> 00:36:59.309
Er, yeah, but...

555
00:36:59.376 --> 00:37:00.912
Well, so he
should be here.


556
00:37:01.012 --> 00:37:03.147
It's empty now.
It's the perfect time to do it.


557
00:37:03.213 --> 00:37:07.384
Oh, we refurbish
all the time.
Yeah, tourism is eating
this ship alive.


558
00:37:07.417 --> 00:37:09.120
People come, they take things.

559
00:37:09.286 --> 00:37:11.723
Souvenirs that cost
us a fortune.


560
00:37:13.057 --> 00:37:14.391
You know the worst offender?

561
00:37:14.559 --> 00:37:17.061
I mean, you'll laugh.

562
00:37:17.161 --> 00:37:18.162
Mould.

563
00:37:18.196 --> 00:37:19.429
-What, mould?
-Hmm.


564
00:37:19.463 --> 00:37:21.933
Such a tiny nuisance, you know.

565
00:37:22.432 --> 00:37:24.736
We got leaking roofs,
dripping air ducts,


566
00:37:24.769 --> 00:37:28.472
sweating plumbing pipes
and all this...damp.


567
00:37:29.140 --> 00:37:31.441
I mean, you wouldn't think it
when you're up there
in the fresh air.


568
00:37:31.475 --> 00:37:33.243
But below deck
is the perfect breeding ground


569
00:37:33.276 --> 00:37:36.647
for some really...
nasty organisms.


570
00:37:37.548 --> 00:37:40.952
Which might explain
why your son is sick.


571
00:37:40.985 --> 00:37:43.253
Tell me, did Lukas
mention the ship
when you got home?


572
00:37:43.286 --> 00:37:45.455
He said he left his camera
in the pool area.


573
00:37:45.489 --> 00:37:47.424
-Pool?
-His clothes were wet.


574
00:37:47.457 --> 00:37:49.193
No, pockets of stagnant water.

575
00:37:49.227 --> 00:37:50.628
Poor ventilation.

576
00:37:50.828 --> 00:37:51.863
He said the pool.

577
00:37:51.896 --> 00:37:54.098
When we docked in '67,
the boilers came out,


578
00:37:54.132 --> 00:37:55.566
so did the pool above it.

579
00:37:55.600 --> 00:37:58.703
It was a tragedy, really.
She was a real pearl. But...


580
00:37:59.504 --> 00:38:03.306
Look, er, I know this
isn't the same
without Lukas.


581
00:38:03.641 --> 00:38:05.342
So how about when you come back,

582
00:38:05.375 --> 00:38:08.679
I'll give you a deluxe,
all access, tour.


583
00:38:08.880 --> 00:38:10.248
With me as your guide, yeah?

584
00:38:10.447 --> 00:38:13.050
And, er, this is you.

585
00:38:14.719 --> 00:38:18.421
I had to leave my
very sick son...
at home


586
00:38:19.090 --> 00:38:23.326
in order to come here
because he knows this is, um...


587
00:38:24.427 --> 00:38:26.164
a last chance for us.

588
00:38:26.864 --> 00:38:29.934
I even had to call my very
unpleasant mother


589
00:38:30.134 --> 00:38:31.468
to ask her to watch him.

590
00:38:31.836 --> 00:38:35.640
And as you can imagine,
I don't like calling
her for anything.


591
00:38:36.674 --> 00:38:39.442
We are just not leaving here
empty handed...


592
00:38:40.711 --> 00:38:41.913
Captain.

593
00:38:43.714 --> 00:38:47.552
I am not asking you,
I am begging you.


594
00:38:48.318 --> 00:38:49.520
Okay.

595
00:38:50.922 --> 00:38:51.989
Okay!

596
00:38:52.924 --> 00:38:57.028
But, er, anything below M deck
is restricted.


597
00:38:57.795 --> 00:39:00.363
He's not exactly Captain
material,
is he?


598
00:39:07.939 --> 00:39:10.608
If you don't wanna do this,
I understand.


599
00:39:12.475 --> 00:39:15.412
I'm here, aren't I?

600
00:39:39.503 --> 00:39:41.639
Your mask, Sir. Remove it.

601
00:39:41.672 --> 00:39:44.075
My mask?
What does that have to
do with anything?


602
00:39:44.141 --> 00:39:45.810
There is a special place in hell

603
00:39:46.177 --> 00:39:48.246
for men who impersonate
war heroes.


604
00:39:53.784 --> 00:39:56.020
If you're not who
you claim to be,
then who are you?


605
00:40:01.491 --> 00:40:05.529
Should anything happen
to your father or I, stay here.


606
00:40:07.430 --> 00:40:08.431
Come with me, Sir.

607
00:40:08.465 --> 00:40:09.901
What on earth are you doing?

608
00:40:09.934 --> 00:40:11.903
Give me your hands. Come on.

609
00:40:13.170 --> 00:40:16.674
...just see what she can do.
Just see what she can do.


610
00:40:19.577 --> 00:40:21.145
♪Might be a curse♪

611
00:40:21.279 --> 00:40:24.081
♪It makes your mind
all into a blur♪


612
00:40:24.148 --> 00:40:25.950
♪You won't be feeling...♪

613
00:40:27.985 --> 00:40:33.423
Your, er, film, One
Up, One Down.
Didn't think much of it.


614
00:40:34.091 --> 00:40:35.960
The plot wasn't very realistic.

615
00:40:36.160 --> 00:40:38.162
Oh, a critic.

616
00:40:38.863 --> 00:40:42.733
This, no doubt, is why
he hides his face.


617
00:40:48.639 --> 00:40:50.341
A parent would do anything
for their child.


618
00:40:50.508 --> 00:40:53.411
Even if it requires looking
rather...foolish.


619
00:41:00.985 --> 00:41:03.754
Enjoy the rest
of your evening.


620
00:41:13.030 --> 00:41:15.967
I told you, I told you,
I told you he'd be there.


621
00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:17.301
-Darling.
-Yeah?


622
00:41:17.401 --> 00:41:18.836
-Your mask.
-Oh.


623
00:41:21.706 --> 00:41:23.074
D'you think she bought it?

624
00:41:23.107 --> 00:41:24.508
-Yes.
-Hmm.


625
00:41:24.542 --> 00:41:25.843
You were magnificent.

626
00:41:26.010 --> 00:41:28.245
A little part of me feels bad
we had to lie.


627
00:41:28.346 --> 00:41:30.548
How else is she supposed
to learn
to perform when it counts?


628
00:41:30.581 --> 00:41:33.851
Still, it's one thing to have an
opportunity, it's another
to take it.


629
00:41:33.918 --> 00:41:35.252
And she will.

630
00:41:35.286 --> 00:41:36.454
With her talent,

631
00:41:36.620 --> 00:41:39.890
she won't need to scrimp
and scrape like we did.


632
00:41:40.858 --> 00:41:43.728
Every door will be held open,
every opportunity laid out


633
00:41:43.761 --> 00:41:46.030
before she even sets
foot off this ship.


634
00:41:49.633 --> 00:41:51.302
I'll see you back in the cabin.

635
00:41:51.369 --> 00:41:54.205
Yeah.

636
00:41:54.238 --> 00:41:56.741
How did you know that
she'd pick the fortune card?


637
00:42:10.388 --> 00:42:12.089
Shit.

638
00:42:12.890 --> 00:42:19.230
♪The bells of hell are
ting-a-ling-a-ling
for you but not for me♪


639
00:42:49.494 --> 00:42:52.063
Excuse me.
Do Dinosaurs on Ice Skates.


640
00:42:53.764 --> 00:42:56.000
Apologies for my friend earlier.

641
00:42:56.233 --> 00:42:57.635
Was your father in the army?

642
00:42:57.735 --> 00:43:00.304
Yes. He was in the Varlets.

643
00:43:00.337 --> 00:43:02.273
So, he entertained the troops.

644
00:43:02.640 --> 00:43:04.341
Sounds like a hero to me!

645
00:43:06.444 --> 00:43:08.813
Well, here's the thing.

646
00:43:09.814 --> 00:43:14.285
I wanted to ask
if you'd mind a dance.


647
00:43:16.620 --> 00:43:18.322
Mr Astaire!

648
00:43:18.422 --> 00:43:20.357
Please, call me Fred.

649
00:43:20.391 --> 00:43:22.460
Fred. I'm your biggest fan!

650
00:43:22.561 --> 00:43:23.562
You are?!

651
00:43:23.727 --> 00:43:27.031
Well, I think that's
made my day.


652
00:44:12.910 --> 00:44:14.812
If you wanna
sleep, I'll wait.


653
00:44:15.446 --> 00:44:16.780
Could be a long night.

654
00:44:18.415 --> 00:44:19.783
I'm fine.

655
00:44:22.653 --> 00:44:24.054
Are you sure?

656
00:44:26.525 --> 00:44:27.791
Yeah.

657
00:44:47.178 --> 00:44:48.846
Urgh.

658
00:44:50.481 --> 00:44:51.849
Are you hungry?

659
00:44:54.218 --> 00:44:55.719
Not really.

660
00:44:57.354 --> 00:44:58.722
I might look around

661
00:44:58.756 --> 00:45:01.192
and see if I can find
a vending machine or something.


662
00:45:05.564 --> 00:45:06.830
Yeah, I know.

663
00:45:13.304 --> 00:45:14.872
We have to talk about it.

664
00:45:15.674 --> 00:45:19.710
I'm still trying to, you know,
process everything
you've told me.


665
00:45:19.743 --> 00:45:22.279
But I, I, I can't
get my head around it.


666
00:45:23.747 --> 00:45:26.050
-I...
-Maybe later?


667
00:45:29.588 --> 00:45:30.955
Yeah.

668
00:45:45.503 --> 00:45:48.906
Honey! We leave
for Long Beach
in five minutes!


669
00:45:53.110 --> 00:45:54.278
Lukas?

670
00:46:06.691 --> 00:46:08.225
Is everything okay?

671
00:46:10.861 --> 00:46:12.763
Oh my God,
what are you doing?!


672
00:46:16.934 --> 00:46:18.202
Where is she?!

673
00:46:18.269 --> 00:46:19.803
She said she'd find me!

674
00:46:21.839 --> 00:46:23.040
Just come inside.

675
00:46:23.207 --> 00:46:25.577
I'm never
going back in that ship!


676
00:46:25.610 --> 00:46:28.345
Take my hand,
please. Lukas.


677
00:46:28.379 --> 00:46:29.648
That's not my name!

678
00:47:00.044 --> 00:47:04.048
♪Oh, Death, where is thy
sting-a-ling-a-ling?♪


679
00:47:04.081 --> 00:47:06.817
Oh, grave, thy victory

680
00:47:06.950 --> 00:47:11.188
♪The bells of hell
go ting-a-ling-
a-ling for you...♪


681
00:47:22.866 --> 00:47:24.968
♪...but not for me.♪

682
00:47:53.864 --> 00:47:59.203
Set alarm, forty-five minutes.
Set, sleep calm...


683
00:48:02.106 --> 00:48:03.474
Hello.

684
00:48:03.842 --> 00:48:08.112
Tonight, let's go to
a far-off place.


685
00:48:09.046 --> 00:48:11.850
Using my words in your dreams.

686
00:48:11.982 --> 00:48:16.920
Where time dissolves
like shifting desert sands.


687
00:49:09.072 --> 00:49:12.777
...and the truth of
what happened.


688
00:49:15.379 --> 00:49:20.685
Now, focus
on the dark.


689
00:49:35.867 --> 00:49:37.234
Bingo.

690
00:50:05.597 --> 00:50:06.831
Come on...

691
00:50:20.444 --> 00:50:21.713
Urgh!

692
00:50:21.746 --> 00:50:28.352
Urgh. Urgh. Argh.

693
00:50:38.930 --> 00:50:40.430
Come on!

694
00:50:40.698 --> 00:50:42.032
Urgh!

695
00:50:48.573 --> 00:50:49.574
Ha.

696
00:51:09.994 --> 00:51:13.598
Jackie...went...away.

697
00:51:14.464 --> 00:51:17.200
Never...to...return.

698
00:51:19.771 --> 00:51:24.609
Where...is...she?

699
00:51:29.547 --> 00:51:31.816
Where is she?!

700
00:51:31.849 --> 00:51:33.618
I come bearing...

701
00:51:41.291 --> 00:51:43.126
Where is she?

702
00:51:45.295 --> 00:51:46.864
She must've slipped out.

703
00:51:47.065 --> 00:51:50.167
No. I told her to stay here.

704
00:51:52.169 --> 00:51:54.404
-You have to let me inside.
-Out of the question.


705
00:51:54.505 --> 00:51:55.540
Good evening!

706
00:51:55.673 --> 00:51:56.708
Good evening.

707
00:51:56.741 --> 00:51:58.175
Here you are, my man.

708
00:51:59.877 --> 00:52:00.878
Hmm.

709
00:52:14.926 --> 00:52:19.196
...there's a special
guest onboard,
Mr Fred Astaire!


710
00:52:19.530 --> 00:52:22.299
♪There's some that's bound
for New York town♪


711
00:52:22.332 --> 00:52:24.802
♪and some that's bound
for France♪


712
00:52:24.869 --> 00:52:30.675
♪Heave away, me Johnny,
heave away♪


713
00:52:30.742 --> 00:52:33.778
♪And some that's bound
for the bangle bay♪


714
00:52:33.811 --> 00:52:36.146
♪to teach them ways to dance♪

715
00:52:36.179 --> 00:52:39.182
♪Heavy away, me Johnny boy♪

716
00:52:39.349 --> 00:52:42.185
♪We're all bound to go♪

717
00:52:42.219 --> 00:52:45.056
♪The pilot he's a-waiting for♪

718
00:52:45.089 --> 00:52:47.391
♪the turning of the tide♪

719
00:52:47.424 --> 00:52:53.330
♪Heavy away, me Johnny,
heave away♪


720
00:52:53.430 --> 00:52:56.166
♪And then me boys
will be gone again♪


721
00:52:56.199 --> 00:52:58.770
♪with a good and westerly wind♪

722
00:52:58.836 --> 00:53:01.973
♪Heave away, me Johnny boy,♪

723
00:53:02.073 --> 00:53:06.811
♪ We're all bound to go♪

724
00:54:43.708 --> 00:54:46.511
Captain, you're risking
the forward generators


725
00:54:46.544 --> 00:54:48.478
and the safety of
the passengers!


726
00:54:50.047 --> 00:54:51.149
And for what?

727
00:54:51.182 --> 00:54:53.217
For the sake of a title?
It's reckless.


728
00:54:53.483 --> 00:54:55.586
The first-class pool
is above us.


729
00:54:56.020 --> 00:54:58.055
Clear it out, as a precaution.

730
00:54:58.488 --> 00:54:59.924
If that'll make you feel better.

731
00:54:59.991 --> 00:55:01.259
But I'm telling you,

732
00:55:01.626 --> 00:55:05.395
there's nothing we can
throw at this ship
that she cannot survive.


733
00:55:09.033 --> 00:55:10.835
Natural law might disagree.

734
00:55:50.107 --> 00:55:51.509
Ow!

735
00:56:35.820 --> 00:56:37.387
Call the doctor!

736
00:56:38.689 --> 00:56:39.991
Emergency in the boiler room!

737
00:57:09.086 --> 00:57:10.755
Fred, you did it again.

738
00:57:20.264 --> 00:57:24.434
Kid, you were wonderful.
Just wonderful!


739
00:57:25.636 --> 00:57:28.406
I am sorry about before.

740
00:57:30.141 --> 00:57:31.142
You got real talent.

741
00:57:31.542 --> 00:57:32.743
I want to offer you a contract.

742
00:57:32.777 --> 00:57:34.578
I guarantee it'll open
every door in town,


743
00:57:34.612 --> 00:57:36.847
or I'm not Viktor Kershner!

744
00:57:38.649 --> 00:57:40.483
Now, if I could just
speak to your parents,


745
00:57:40.518 --> 00:57:43.587
straighten out that
misunderstanding
from before.


746
00:57:46.557 --> 00:57:49.527
You stay there.
I'll go talk to them.


747
00:57:51.562 --> 00:57:53.030
Thank you!

748
00:57:53.230 --> 00:57:54.565
Kid, you earned it.

